    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the overview. it's a bit too high-level for a competitive policy debate though. my students need more philosophical and structural depth to win rounds. \n\ncan you expand on the \"national sovereignty\" point? specifically, how does the concept of Westphalian sovereignty or the social contract theory support the idea that a state has a moral and legal obligation to strictly control its borders? go deep on the logic there.",
